	<TD WIDTH="20%"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000">Author</FONT></TD>
	<TD><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="2"COLOR="#000000">New guild position, the Herald</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cdcdcd" ALIGN="LEFT">
<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="sans-serif" COLOR="#000000"><b>Rohwin</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000"><B></B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Joined: Jun 03, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Posts: 93</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">From: Freeport<br></FONT></td><TD><img src="/forums/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000">Posted: 2002-04-10 15:54&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#000000" face="sans-serif">Well met everyone,<BR><BR>The High-Council has voted on a new guild position to be created called the "Herald."<BR><BR>The function of the Herald will be to keep track of guild members' status and collect character updates once per month.<BR><BR>Any guild member may volunteer to become the Herald. The House of Lords will vote on which member will get the job. If the Herald is negligent or non-existant then the duties will go to the Regent until a new Herald can be found. <BR><BR>The duties of the Herald will be to contact every member of the guild once a month. The Herald will be provided a mailing list for email, and they will make a post on our forums. Guild members will be asked to either reply to the mail or forum to indicate that they are still a member of the guild. Also, guild members can provide any character updates they wish the web-site to reflect, such as current level. <BR><BR>A deadline of 3 weeks will be allowed to reply to the Herald. The deadline time should be indicated on the mail and forum. Anyone who fails to reply by the deadline will be considered inactive. The Herald will then have the remainder of the month to email the Regent with a list of current and inactive members with any updates. At the beginning of the next month the process will start again. <BR><BR>If a member does not reply then they will be listed as an inactive member. On the following month, if the inactive does not reply again they will be removed from the guild. If a member does reply, and indicates that they wish to remain in the guild as an inactive member, then we will need to know when their approximate return to EverQuest will be. They will not need to be contacted by the Herald until their declared return time comes. The maximum time for a leave of absence is 6 months. Members can extend their leave of absence in 6 month intervals, but we will need to hear their intentions at the conclusion of each period of inactivity. <BR><BR>Members who are inactive may not hold any positions of power in the guild, such as the House of Lords or vouchers, regardless of their political points. When they do return, then they may resume their duties in the guild as their points dictate. <BR><BR>Members who indicate that they have left the guild will of course be removed immediately. <BR><BR>The Herald will earn a reward for taking on these duties. The addditional title of Herald will be bestowed upon him or her while doing the duties. Also, after 6 months and therefore 6 guild member status reports have been successfully submited to the Regent, the Herald will earn 1 political point. Only 1 point can be earned for this duty. After a character has served for 6 months, the Herald may choose to step down to allow a new Herald to be voted in. The House of Lords may remove a current Herald by majority vote if for any reason they choose to do so.<BR><BR>Take care,<BR>
<BR>_________________<BR><img src="/images/rohwinssymbol.gif" width=60 height=42 align=left valign=center alt="Rohwin's Vanguard">Rohwin Amoure Ardour<BR>Regent of Cursus Honorum</FONT><BR>
